      "role": "user",
      "content": "but temporary doesn't mean it's actually fixing anything. it's just a cycle. i've heard the \"it gets better\" and \"reach out\" stuff a million times but it feels like people are just saying it because they're uncomfortable with the truth. the truth is there's nothing there. no meaning, no purpose, just entropy. how can anyone find \"hope\" in a universe that is literally just a cold, empty void?",
